OL,6,FDS Darren Weston, officer in the case,
OL,7,Fspoke of the "extraordinary bravery"
OL,8,Fof the victim.
OL,10,FHe said: "The bravery of the victim to
OL,11,Fcome forward to the police is a
OL,12,Ftestament to her character and trust
OL,13,Fin the criminal justice system.
OL,15,F"She was a child and subjected to
OL,16,Fhorrific crimes at the hands of a
OL,17,Fdangerous man, who refused to accept
OL,18,Fhis actions until he was found guilty
OL,19,Funanimously by a jury.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G6/7
